# Admin Panel Standards (Next.js)

## Tech Stack

- Next.js with App Router
- UI components: shadcn/ui (or similar)
- Forms: react-hook-form + Zod validation
- Charts: Recharts or Chart.js
- Icons: SVG preferred — use `<Image>` or inline SVG

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: design for 320px, enhance up
- Breakpoints: 320px (mobile) → 768px (tablet) → 1024px (desktop)
- Touch targets: minimum 44px for interactive elements

## Required Patterns

- Data tables with sorting, filtering, search, and pagination
- Loading states on all async operations
- Success / error toasts for user actions
- Confirmation modals for destructive actions (delete, ban, etc.)
- Role-based access control (RBAC) on routes and actions
- Audit logs for admin mutations
- CSV / Excel export for data tables
- Real-time updates via WebSocket or polling where needed

## Forms

- All forms validated with Zod schemas
- Inline field-level error messages
- Disable submit button during async operations
- Redirect + success toast on success; error toast on failure

## Components

- Typed props with interfaces — no `any`
- Named exports: `export const DriverTable: React.FC<Props>`
- Colocate related components, hooks, and types
